node.text:
Because we’re moving into summer in Australia and further away from bigger swells I thought I would dig through the archives and start posting some content from over the years. As I sat and watched, I realised how much I’ve changed.

Facing Fear was a piece put together in 2018. It’s so interesting listening to my mindset and my perspective back then. I can hear how young I was, how scared I still was, but how hungry I was to do better and win and how driven I was by results. 

Fast forward a couple of years and I was back out at Jaws in the Women’s final, ending up placing second by 1.49 and very proud of my performance and the waves that I caught that day. 

Today I’m sitting here still very proud of that performance although uncertainty creeps in... With current circumstances I don’t know if I’ll get an opportunity to compete in the Big Wave Challenge or wether or not it will even run... 

But I also sit here with a different perspective now realising that my happiness isn’t bound by a result in a contest but by my intrinsic nature to be better and moments in the ocean that provide me with an intimate connection with nature to remind me of what I belong to, what I am made of and what I am a part of ✨🏄🏼‍♀️ @wsl @wslbigwave

node.text: My morning routine is something that is essential for me to set the tone for my day. Over the last few years it has changed slightly but one thing that has stayed the same is lemon water first thing in the morning and then every other morning I mix in a @usanainc probiotic Usana probiotic supports a healthy digestive system, helps to maintain a healthy gut flora and contains up to 12 billion bacteria per serving. Win the morning, win the day! #liveusana #usana

node.text: This has been something that has been really hard for me to come to terms with and something that’s even harder for me to talk about. But it’s something I’m trying to be more open and honest about as I really think it’s helping me to understand and process how I’m feeling. About five years ago my mum was diagnosed with Frontotemporal dementia (FTD). She was 45 then and in the space of that five years she has deteriorated so fast that she now lives in a high care facility, is immobile, non verbal, can’t shower or feed herself properly and is permanently in a wheel chair. It has effected everything in my life and how I think about life and everyone in my family. It’s been so hard for us to watch, I can’t even imagine how she must feel. This is the first time I’ve ever openly spoken about it. If you’re in a similar situation, I understand, I’m sorry and I sympathise with you. And for everyone else, please don’t ever take your health and family for granted. Go and hug your mum, your family and friends and tell them you love them! Because in the end what else matters? Love ❤️ (This video was a snippet from the podcast “On her Game” with @samsquires where I talk more in depth about my life. If you want to listen to the full podcast click the link in my bio)

node.text:
Here’s a little workout that I do to warm up before a surf session or if I’m not surfing to stay on top of my surf fitness 🏄🏼‍♀️🏄🏼‍♂️ SURF POP UPS - 5 each side
It’s a fundamental movement for surfing but it’s amazing how much this help by just doing it on land. You become so much more fluid, stronger and quicker at popping up.

LATERAL LUNGE TO LATERAL SLIDE (that’s what I call it) - 10 each side 
Do this nice and smoothly and controlled. 
SIT UP - STAND UP - 10 reps 
Amazing for working on your core strength and explosive power, which is crucial for surfing. 
TIGER CRAWL - up and back 
Great for core strength. Hands under shoulders, knees under hips, try and keep your back in a neutral position. Move your opposite arm and opposite leg at the same time. Take it slow to make sure your form is correct. 
PUSHUPS - 10 reps 
I hate pushups and I’m still working on my form with these! But they are a great exercise 😅

BOX JUMPS - 10 reps 
Again great for building explosive power. If I’m at the beach and can’t jump onto anything I’ll just do 10 jump squats on the spot. 
Rest 30secs to 1 min between each exercise. Repeat circuit 3-4 times.

Save me for later ↗️↗️

node.title: Surf Specific workout/warm up - no equipment

node.text:
Little lower body session that I’ve been doing at home that requires no equipment! 🤗💛 SQUATS - 15 reps 
GLUTE BRIDGE - 10 each side 
CLAMSHELL - 15 each side 
GLUTE BRIDGE WITH LEG RAISE - 10 each side 
DONKEY KICKS - 10 each side 
Rest 30secs to 1 min between each exercise. Repeat circuit 2-3 times.

Save me for later ↗️↗️
